&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cancer Pathway Manager (Endoscopy)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a patient centered individual to join the Endoscopy Team in the role of Cancer Pathway Manager. This new role has been developed to ensure that patients with upper and lower cancers receive the diagnostic and treatment they need as quickly and efficiently as possible. You will also be attending the Large Polyp Multi-Disciplinary Team Meeting, liaising with consultants, prepping and taking minutes from the decision of the patients outcome .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support MDT team and clinical teams by ensuring that all key appointments, tests/diagnostic results and treatments are achieved in a timely manner. The cancer pathway manager will assist in delivering upper and lower cancer pathway that is as seamless as possible for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be part of the Endoscopy Business Unit which is part of the Abdominal Medicine and Surgery CSU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Paula Bourke Business Manager paula.bourke1@nhs.net ext 0113 3920698&lt;/p&gt;
